---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="What Democracy 2028 is, why it exists, and who is building it."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <h1>About Democracy 2028</h1>

    <p>
      Democracy 2028 is a grassroots, open-source, evidence-based policy framework for
      strengthening American democracy and governance. It is structured as a comprehensive,
      chapter-by-chapter blueprint covering every federal agency and major policy area.
    </p>

    <h2>What This Is</h2>
    <p>
      This project is modeled on the scope of major policy frameworks like the Heritage
      Foundation's "Project 2025: Mandate for Leadership" — but grounded in democratic
      values, empirical evidence, and constructive governance.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is <strong>not</strong> a partisan document. It draws on research and principles from
      across the political spectrum. The frame is "good governance and democratic accountability,"
      not left versus right.
    </p>

    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>
      Every chapter is written by subject-matter experts, reviewed by practitioners and
      researchers, and published openly under a Creative Commons license. Every factual
      claim has a source. Every recommendation is specific and actionable.
    </p>
    <p>
      The full project is hosted on GitHub. Anyone can propose edits, flag factual errors,
      or apply to write a chapter in their area of expertise.
    </p>

    <h2>License</h2>
    <p>
      All content is published under the{' '}
      <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License (CC BY-SA 4.0)
      </a>.
      You are free to share and adapt the material for any purpose, provided you give
      appropriate credit and distribute your contributions under the same license.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      To contribute, flag an error, or get in touch, the best path is via{' '}
      <a href="https://github.com/democracyproject2028/democracyproject2028" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        GitHub
      </a>.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    margin: 0 0 2rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-navy);
    margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 2px solid var(--color-border);
    padding-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }

  p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: #2D3748;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  a { color: var(--color-navy); }
  a:hover { color: var(--color-gold); }
</style>
